description.narrative:
Expanding Access to Finance for MSEs : Micro and Small Enterprises ("MSEs") play an important role in creating employment and contributing to local economy particularly in less developed regions. Nevertheless, MSEs are under-served by traditional financial institutions.   The expansion of the Companies will help address this issue by increasing credit supply accessible and affordable by MSEs; 

Supporting Economic Growth in Frontier Regions: Frontier regions in China have experienced much  pronounced difficulties in access to finance for MSEs, which hinders the economic growth in these regions. The Companies, operating in three large frontier provinces, i.e., Sichuan, Chongqinq and Hubei, will expand access to credit in these regions, specifically to MSEs, thereby supporting the continued growth of the local economy;

Demonstration Effect of Setting Best Practice in the Burgeoning Chinese Microfinance Sector:    The Companies have potential to become model institutions in China in serving the MSEs with a novel business model.  The success of the Companies is likely to attract other MCCs to emulate, with a demonstration effect to stimulate the healthy development for the entire sector.
